It was an action-packed weekend as supporters of historical rivals Kaizer Chiefs and Orlando Pirates descended on FNB stadium to watch their teams as they went head to head during the Soweto Derby on Saturday. Dressed in their respective clubs' regalia, more than 87,000 fans filled the stadium to capacity. Excitement was high among the supporters as they cheered for their teams. Kaizer Chiefs and Orlando Pirates drew 1-1. Here's what you need to know about the derby: